### Get all Service Requests
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/service-requests/requests/
Accept: application/json

### Create a new Service Request
# IMPORTANT: Replace <user_id> with an actual ID of a User from your Django Admin.
# You can create one via `python manage.py createsuperuser` and log into /admin/.
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/service-requests/requests/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "New Software Installation Request",
    "description": "I need MS Office 365 installed on my new laptop.",
    "requested_by_id": 1,
    "assigned_to_id": null,
    "category": "software",
    "priority": "medium"
}

### Create another Service Request
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/service-requests/requests/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Guest Wi-Fi Access for Conference",
    "description": "Please provide temporary guest Wi-Fi access for 50 attendees for the 'Future Tech' conference.",
    "requested_by_id": 1,
    "assigned_to_id": 1,
    "category": "network",
    "priority": "high"
}

### Get a single Service Request by ID (Replace <request_id> with an actual ID from your POST response)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/service-requests/requests/SR-AA-0001/
Accept: application/json

### Update a Service Request (Replace <request_id> and modify fields as needed)
PATCH http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/service-requests/requests/SR-AA-0001/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "in_progress",
    "assigned_to_id": 1,
    "resolution_notes": "Assigned to IT Team Lead."
}

### Delete a Service Request (Replace <request_id>)
# DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/service-requests/requests/SR-AA-0001/
# Accept: application/json